    "en": {
      "title": "The gas ship will arrive today - President's advice to officials",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The President's Media Division says that the first ship carrying 3,700 metric tons of gas has reached the coast of this country. Also, the second ship carrying 3,740 metric tons of gas is scheduled to arrive in the island tomorrow (11) evening, according to the announcement issued by the Presidential Media Division.",
        "President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has instructed the officials to carry out the unloading and distribution of gas as soon as the first ship arrives at Kerawalapitiya today (10) at 3 pm.",
        "The third ship with 3,200 metric tons of gas will arrive in Sri Lanka on July (15) and the amount of gas ordered for this month is 33,000 metric tons.",
        "Mr. Muditha Peiris, president of Litro, says that the gas distribution will be regular and systematic from July 12 and the problem regarding domestic gas demand will be completely avoided by the end of this month."
      ],
